      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "access",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The access object to which to add the information."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "applicationList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "An array of trusted application objects (that is, "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/sectrustedapplicationref"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " instances) identifying applications that are allowed access to the keychain item without user confirmation. Use the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/1400622-sectrustedapplicationcreatefromp"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " function to create trusted application objects. If you set this parameter to "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "NULL"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", then any application can use this item. If you pass an empty array, then there are no trusted applications. Call the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corefoundation/1521153-cfrelease"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " function to release this object when you are finished using it."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "description",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The human readable name to be used to refer to this item when the user is prompted."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "promptSelector",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A pointer to a prompt selector. If you set the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "CSSM_ACL_KEYCHAIN_PROMPT_REQUIRE_PASSPHRASE"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " bit, the user is prompted for the keychain password each time a non-trusted application attempts to access this item, even if the keychain is already unlocked."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "newAcl",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "On return, points to an access control list object, which is a reference to the new access control list entry."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return_value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A result code. See "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/1542001-security_framework_result_codes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The ACL object returned by this function is a reference to an access control list (ACL) entry. The ACL entry includes a list of trusted applications (see "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/1400622-sectrustedapplicationcreatefromp"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "), the name of the keychain item as it appears in user prompts, the prompt selector flag, and a list of one or more operations to which this ACL entry applies. By default, a new ACL entry applies to all operations (the CSSM authorization tag is set to "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "CSSM_ACL_AUTHORIZATION_ANY"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "). Use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/1577130-secaclsetauthorizations"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function to set the list of operations for an ACL object. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The system allows exactly one owner ACL entry in each access object. The "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "SecACLCreateFromSimpleContents"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function fails if you attempt to add a second owner ACL. To change owner access controls, use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/1521111-secaccesscopyselectedacllist"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function to find the owner ACL (that is, the only ACL with a CSSM authorization tag of "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "CSSM_ACL_AUTHORIZATION_CHANGE_ACL"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ") and the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/1577129-secaclsetsimplecontents"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function to change it as needed."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Special Considerations",
          "anchor": "1676754"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This function is deprecated in macOS 10.7 and later; use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/1402295-secaclcreatewithsimplecontents"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " instead."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
